00:34:05.890 --> 00:34:10.100
It's always going to help
get over that barrier.

00:34:10.100 --> 00:34:14.400
But increase the temperature,
increase the rate.

00:34:14.400 --> 00:34:17.980
But for an overall
reaction, temperature

00:34:17.980 --> 00:34:20.940
is a little more
complicated to predict.

00:34:20.940 --> 00:34:23.510
So if you increase
the temperature,

00:34:23.510 --> 00:34:26.529
it's not always as clear what's
going to happen to the rate.

00:34:26.529 --> 00:34:28.820
Because you can have a lot
of different steps involved.

00:34:28.820 --> 00:34:30.449
It can be exothermic
and endothermic.

00:34:30.449 --> 00:34:32.219
A lot can be happening.

00:34:32.219 --> 00:34:35.000
Changing the temperature,
you're changing k.

00:34:35.000 --> 00:34:38.190
So to think about
an overall reaction,

00:34:38.190 --> 00:34:40.326
we need to understand
reaction mechanisms.

00:34:40.326 --> 00:34:42.159
And that's really
convenient because we just

00:34:42.159 --> 00:34:44.980
talked about reaction
mechanisms on Monday.

00:34:44.980 --> 00:34:48.250
So you all know how to write
out reaction mechanisms.

00:34:48.250 --> 00:34:50.430
So let's just practice.

00:34:50.430 --> 00:34:52.180
So for this example,
we have two molecules

00:34:52.180 --> 00:34:55.775
of N O plus O2 going to 2NO2.

00:34:55.775 --> 00:34:58.830
Step one, fast and reversible.

00:34:58.830 --> 00:35:02.320
N O plus N O, going
to an intermediate.

00:35:02.320 --> 00:35:03.840
Then the intermediate
is reacting

00:35:03.840 --> 00:35:08.260
with oxygen going to two
molecules of our product.

00:35:08.260 --> 00:35:10.420
So we can write the
rate of formation

00:35:10.420 --> 00:35:12.670
of product based
on the slow step,

00:35:12.670 --> 00:35:14.420
or if we didn't
know the slow set,

00:35:14.420 --> 00:35:17.370
on the second step
or the last step.

00:35:17.370 --> 00:35:20.360
So two molecules, again, two
molecules are being formed.

00:35:20.360 --> 00:35:23.960
k2 times the concentration
of the intermediate times

00:35:23.960 --> 00:35:27.060
the concentration of O2.

00:35:27.060 --> 00:35:30.439
But we have an intermediate.

00:35:30.439 --> 00:35:32.480
So we need to solve for
the intermediate in terms

00:35:32.480 --> 00:35:36.610
of rate constants,
reactants, and products.

00:35:36.610 --> 00:35:39.690
But now we're told we
have a fast step followed

00:35:39.690 --> 00:35:40.800
by a slow step.

00:35:40.800 --> 00:35:43.390
So we know how to do this.

00:35:43.390 --> 00:35:46.100
And remember, when you have a
fast, reversible step followed

00:35:46.100 --> 00:35:51.680
by a slow step, this first step
approximates an equilibrium

00:35:51.680 --> 00:35:52.540
reaction.

00:35:52.540 --> 00:35:54.720
There is not much of the
intermediate that's being

00:35:54.720 --> 00:35:56.187
siphoned off in the slow step.

00:35:56.187 --> 00:35:58.145
So pretty much, when you
form the intermediate,

00:35:58.145 --> 00:36:00.330
it's going back and
forth just like you have

00:36:00.330 --> 00:36:03.050
in an equilibrium situation.

00:36:03.050 --> 00:36:06.690
And just to emphasize this,
I'll share a little picture

00:36:06.690 --> 00:36:08.890
here of the beach in
the summer when you

00:36:08.890 --> 00:36:10.680
don't need your winter coat.

00:36:10.680 --> 00:36:14.440
And here we have my daughter
and her best friend.

00:36:14.440 --> 00:36:16.400
And they are trying
to empty the ocean

00:36:16.400 --> 00:36:18.950
with this princess bucket.

00:36:18.950 --> 00:36:22.590
And one can ask the question, is
this going to affect the tides?

00:36:22.590 --> 00:36:24.480
Is the ocean going
to be different?

00:36:24.480 --> 00:36:26.790
But the rate at which
my daughter and Aiden

00:36:26.790 --> 00:36:30.460
fill up their buckets
and bring them over here,

00:36:30.460 --> 00:36:33.370
that's a really slow step
compared to everything

00:36:33.370 --> 00:36:35.230
that's going on in the ocean.

00:36:35.230 --> 00:36:38.400
So when you have a very
slow step like a kid

00:36:38.400 --> 00:36:41.050
and a long distance
with a princess pail,

00:36:41.050 --> 00:36:43.070
you don't really need
to worry about that.

00:36:43.070 --> 00:36:46.230
And you can think about the fast
step as being an equilibrium.

00:36:46.230 --> 00:36:49.480
This is not being siphoned
off enough to worry about it.

00:36:49.480 --> 00:36:54.350
And so that makes it easier
to solve for your intermediate

00:36:54.350 --> 00:36:57.470
because then you can just do it
by an equilibrium expression.

00:36:57.470 --> 00:37:01.160
So in the clicker question,
