00:38:23.190 --> 00:38:25.940
didn't get it written down.

00:38:25.940 --> 00:38:29.690
Now let's think of what
happens with temperature.

00:38:29.690 --> 00:38:33.300
So this is an elementary
rate constant, little k2.

00:38:33.300 --> 00:38:36.330
So you increase the rate when
you increase temperature.

00:38:39.180 --> 00:38:41.150
And here is our
expression again that

00:38:41.150 --> 00:38:44.490
tells us about that change.

00:38:44.490 --> 00:38:48.920
So now for the
equilibrium constant,

00:38:48.920 --> 00:38:51.500
the effect of
temperature depends on

00:38:51.500 --> 00:38:55.350
whether the reaction is
exothermic or endothermic.

00:38:55.350 --> 00:39:00.230
And does anyone remember
